{"pageProps":{"note":{"id":"L1h6IBoBz1ZPj32AZmiIV","title":"Supervised Learning","desc":"","updated":1644232134803,"created":1644230744064,"custom":{},"fname":"science.stats.Supervised Learning","type":"note","vault":{"fsPath":"vault"},"contentHash":"9e745b48d6daf0893829bba3077953b0","links":[{"type":"wiki","from":{"fname":"science.stats.Supervised Learning","id":"L1h6IBoBz1ZPj32AZmiIV","vaultName":"vault"},"value":"science.stats.Regression","alias":"science.stats.Regression","position":{"start":{"line":3,"column":34,"offset":35},"end":{"line":3,"column":62,"offset":63},"indent":[]},"xvault":false,"sameFile":false,"to":{"fname":"science.stats.Regression"}},{"type":"wiki","from":{"fname":"science.stats.Supervised Learning","id":"L1h6IBoBz1ZPj32AZmiIV","vaultName":"vault"},"value":"science.stats.Regression.Loss Functions","alias":"science.stats.Regression.Loss Functions","position":{"start":{"line":9,"column":11,"offset":177},"end":{"line":9,"column":54,"offset":220},"indent":[]},"xvault":false,"sameFile":false,"to":{"fname":"science.stats.Regression.Loss Functions"}},{"type":"wiki","from":{"fname":"science.stats.Supervised Learning","id":"L1h6IBoBz1ZPj32AZmiIV","vaultName":"vault"},"value":"science.stats.Regression.Linear Regression","alias":"science.stats.Regression.Linear Regression","position":{"start":{"line":16,"column":18,"offset":426},"end":{"line":16,"column":64,"offset":472},"indent":[]},"xvault":false,"sameFile":false,"to":{"fname":"science.stats.Regression.Linear Regression"}},{"type":"wiki","from":{"fname":"science.stats.Supervised Learning","id":"L1h6IBoBz1ZPj32AZmiIV","vaultName":"vault"},"value":"science.stats.Support Vector Machines","alias":"science.stats.Support Vector Machines","position":{"start":{"line":18,"column":39,"offset":573},"end":{"line":18,"column":80,"offset":614},"indent":[]},"xvault":false,"sameFile":false,"to":{"fname":"science.stats.Support Vector Machines"}}],"anchors":{"empirical-risk-minimization":{"type":"header","text":"Empirical Risk Minimization","value":"empirical-risk-minimization","line":13,"column":0,"depth":1},"examples-of-hypothesis-classes":{"type":"header","text":"Examples of hypothesis classes","value":"examples-of-hypothesis-classes","line":20,"column":0,"depth":1}},"children":[],"parent":"DrDDAM98fbdfBEotQX5EQ","data":{},"schema":{"schemaId":"vaqh3HhBopTItKNhaLoS9","moduleId":"science"}},"body":"<h1 id=\"supervised-learning\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading\" href=\"#supervised-learning\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\"><use xlink:href=\"#svg-link\"></use></svg></a>Supervised Learning</h1>\n<p>In practice extremely similar to <a href=\"/PublicPersonalKnowledgeBase/notes/WVmDKXo77X0kLJ3l4guEu\">Regression</a>.</p>\n<p>ML is more of a 'curve-fitting' than a 'probability-based' approach.</p>\n<h1 id=\"empirical-risk-minimization\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading\" href=\"#empirical-risk-minimization\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\"><use xlink:href=\"#svg-link\"></use></svg></a>Empirical Risk Minimization</h1>\n<p>We have a <a href=\"/PublicPersonalKnowledgeBase/notes/pBIMmRuN5zKHlVDIWn2wt\">Loss Functions</a>. The risk then is the\nexpected loss of the model across the possible imputs. </p>\n<p> At all points we consider a certain class of functions <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"script\">H</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\mathcal{H}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathcal\" style=\"margin-right:0.00965em;\">H</span></span></span></span></span></p>\n<h1 id=\"examples-of-hypothesis-classes\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading\" href=\"#examples-of-hypothesis-classes\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\"><use xlink:href=\"#svg-link\"></use></svg></a>Examples of hypothesis classes</h1>\n<ul>\n<li>Linear models <a href=\"/PublicPersonalKnowledgeBase/notes/YSgeu1I7ZeKOAKUbvuL8M\">Linear Regression</a></li>\n<li>Linear models, but with nonlinear fixed feature expansions</li>\n<li>Reproducing Kernel Hilbert Spaces (<a href=\"/PublicPersonalKnowledgeBase/notes/umOp2D0HQ0Bmc8vGfWOqk\">Support Vector Machines</a>) </li>\n</ul>","noteIndex":{"id":"wn8PE1RhG0znK1alrGFYv","title":"Root","desc":"","updated":1647507231129,"created":1631901573363,"custom":{"nav_order":0,"permalink":"/"},"fname":"root","type":"note","vault":{"fsPath":"vault"},"contentHash":"db285659ccac8b133c384de1ef51de66","links":[],"anchors":{"welcome-to-stefans-notes":{"type":"header","text":"Welcome to Stefan's Notes!","value":"welcome-to-stefans-notes","line":7,"column":0,"depth":1}},"children":["mxzxxu8z4e6krz99ht96y9d","W1EOZ27Tqx6RbiA2aW3DI","DyoLE2kwm9rRfRZhBGxPW","idhfogizmtcmvaamtalp3o3","4w8wBCSRvYUnGIZeozW03","vB321AipYCs6ldVC0APs9","h6WVdl1UTWVXeWuMJSZ1f","bth6m0exy9q9loxib1mc4al","4abAmH56ausbldEJbZokx","JyOFJ5NTPSVWMfiDy951X","0OO7fjCpcaGZg5qDRZr8z","138666663","pohXgII67dAxnoufG7yAP","42r6290iqzLPmg9BY7fIp","3hoLerNJHjNkDziIKlFF2","T6meT3UNw0nRorEbzoPSl","hIOTXIIBj3vmhG1xc91lA","tnFlQuOAGPkbU2fZI7Cb1","Jb3w3f4x8kixLhrjUW6S1","LV6q5jlD2xtCF6yYFEqFC","ENDcCZFjAW9h66eDoFg7I","b5IeREnsTbeggC7rmWV0p","nbBlQzRv6upNd7EAsifqo","xcJ4vbwPtrOHtYsSgUaQi","D41QyIueG2TcjTWPyDwAs","3Gihb6jm1N7h9TvHP0b3m","d9qyiiGgDJAIdYBgV8NHB","OA3izVK70lO3wm3AQ9ac0","srwEq3ZSQj5S0POsjEszf","h1ME0EUHZQrdOQWdI83oP"],"parent":null,"data":{},"body":"# Welcome to Stefan's Notes!\n\n        \n\nLast updated: 2021.12.30\n"},"collectionChildren":null,"customHeadContent":null,"config":{"version":4,"useFMTitle":true,"useNoteTitleForLink":true,"mermaid":true,"useKatex":true,"dev":{"enablePreviewV2":true},"site":{"copyAssets":true,"siteHierarchies":["root"],"siteRootDir":"docs","siteUrl":"https://petrovs12.github.io","ass